                    <span>This is the book which sparked the spiritual revolution in Ghandi, and helped make him the unbelieveable man he was.  Ghandi raved about this book in his autobiography, and I couldn't agree more.  This could quite possibly be the best book I have ever read.  However, two years ago I wouldn't have gotten all that I have out of it.  It came in the perfect time of my spiritual awakening.  By the very Truth of you reading what I am saying  I would suggest you get this book RIGHT NOW!  You are ready to hear what he has to say, and it will make you a better person and thus making our world better.  Tolstoy is a remarkable spiritual revolutionist, and he will open your eyes to the works of others that have been suppressed throughout time.  Good luck to you and take care out there!</span>
                  
              
